<div class="container py-5">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-lg-8">
            <h1 class="text-center mb-4">
                <i class="fas fa-shield-alt text-primary me-3"></i>Privacy Policy
            </h1>
            <p class="text-center text-muted mb-5">
                Because even family flea markets need the fine print ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è
            </p>

            <div class="card shadow-sm">
                <div class="card-body p-5">

                    <div class="alert alert-info border-0 mb-4">
                        <i class="fas fa-info-circle me-2"></i>
                        <strong>TL;DR:</strong> We're not evil data-harvesting overlords. We're just trying to help you sell that weird lamp you've been storing in your garage for 3 years.
                    </div>

                    <h3 class="text-primary mb-3">
                        <i class="fas fa-users me-2"></i>Who We Are
                    </h3>
                    <p>Welcome to <strong>Flea Market by Beloved Websites</strong> - your friendly neighborhood, invite-only marketplace for friends and family. Think of us as that one cousin who's really good at organizing garage sales, except we live on the internet.</p>

                    <h3 class="text-primary mb-3 mt-5">
                        <i class="fas fa-door-open me-2"></i>The Invite-Only Club
                    </h3>
                    <p>This isn't Facebook Marketplace where randos can contact you about your vintage toaster. We're invite-only, which means:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>You need a special password to join (it's probably something embarrassing from our shared history)</li>
                        <li>Only people we actually know and trust can see your stuff</li>
                        <li>No weird strangers asking if you'll take $5 for your $200 bicycle</li>
                        <li>Maximum awkwardness when Aunt Martha tries to lowball your couch</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 class="text-primary mb-3 mt-5">
                        <i class="fas fa-database me-2"></i>What We Collect (And Why)
                    </h3>

                    <h5 class="mb-3">üìß Your Email Address</h5>
                    <p><strong>Why we need it:</strong> So you can log in and so we can send you important stuff like "Hey, someone wants to buy your thing!"</p>
                    <p><strong>What we DON'T do:</strong> Sell it to spam companies or sign you up for weird newsletters about miracle weight loss supplements.</p>

                    <h5 class="mb-3 mt-4">üì∏ Your Item Photos & Descriptions</h5>
                    <p><strong>Why we need it:</strong> Kind of hard to run a marketplace without knowing what you're selling.</p>
                    <p><strong>Fun fact:</strong> We promise not to judge your collection of ceramic frogs or that exercise bike you definitely used more than twice.</p>

                    <h5 class="mb-3 mt-4">üë§ Your Profile Info</h5>
                    <p><strong>What we store:</strong> Your name, profile picture (if you upload one), and any external login info (like Google or Facebook).</p>
                    <p><strong>Why:</strong> So people know who's selling what, and so we can show your beautiful face next to your listings (or your pet's face, we don't discriminate).</p>

                    <h5 class="mb-3 mt-4">üìã Your Activity</h5>
                    <p><strong>What we track:</strong> What you list, what you reserve, basic website usage stuff.</p>
                    <p><strong>What we DON'T track:</strong> How long you stare at that vintage lamp before deciding you actually want to keep it after all.</p>

                    <h3 class="text-primary mb-3 mt-5">
                        <i class="fas fa-share-alt me-2"></i>Who We Share Your Info With
                    </h3>

                    <div class="alert alert-success border-0">
                        <h5 class="mb-3">The Short Answer: Nobody. üéâ</h5>
                        <p class="mb-0">Seriously. We don't sell your data, we don't rent it out, we don't trade it for coffee money. Your info stays in our little family circle where it belongs.</p>
                    </div>

                    <p class="mt-3"><strong>The only exceptions:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Legal Requirements:</strong> If a UK court or law enforcement agency orders us to hand over data (hopefully this never happens in our cozy family marketplace)</li>
                        <li><strong>Safety & Legal Compliance:</strong> If someone's doing something illegal or dangerous (like trying to sell stolen goods or that expired milk from 2019)</li>
                        <li><strong>Technical Services:</strong> Our hosting provider sees some technical data, but they're bound by strict agreements under UK data protection law and probably don't care about your ceramic frog collection anyway</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 class="text-primary mb-3 mt-5">
                        <i class="fas fa-cookie-bite me-2"></i>Cookies (The Digital Kind)
                    </h3>
                    <p>Yes, we use cookies. No, not the chocolate chip kind (sadly). These help us:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Remember that you're logged in</li>
                        <li>Keep your preferences</li>
                        <li>Make the site work properly</li>
                        <li>Analyze how people use the site (in a totally non-creepy, anonymous way)</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>Most browsers let you disable cookies, but then the site might work about as well as a chocolate teapot.</p>

                    <h3 class="text-primary mb-3 mt-5">
                        <i class="fas fa-lock me-2"></i>How We Protect Your Stuff
                    </h3>
                    <p>We take security seriously (even if we joke around about everything else):</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> Your data is encrypted like a secret diary with a really good lock</li>
                        <li><strong>Secure Hosting:</strong> We use reputable hosting services, not Bob's Discount Server Barn</li>
                        <li><strong>Regular Updates:</strong> We keep our software updated faster than you update your phone</li>
                        <li><strong>Limited Access:</strong> Only necessary people can access your data, and they're all people we trust not to gossip about your shopping habits</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 class="text-primary mb-3 mt-5">
                        <i class="fas fa-edit me-2"></i>Your Rights Under UK GDPR (Yes, You Have Them!)
                    </h3>

                    <p>Under UK data protection law, you have several rights. Here they are in plain English:</p>

                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-md-6">
                            <div class="card bg-light border-0 h-100">
                                <div class="card-body">
                                    <h6 class="text-primary">‚úÖ Right of Access</h6>
                                    <p class="small mb-0">Want to see what we have on you? Just ask! We'll send you a copy faster than you can say "ceramic frog collection." We have 1 month to respond (but we'll try to be much quicker).</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-6">
                            <div class="card bg-light border-0 h-100">
                                <div class="card-body">
                                    <h6 class="text-primary">üîß Right to Rectification</h6>
                                    <p class="small mb-0">Notice we spelled your name wrong? Think your profile makes you look like a serial ceramic frog collector? Let us know and we'll fix it!</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="row mt-3">
                        <div class="col-md-6">
                            <div class="card bg-light border-0 h-100">
                                <div class="card-body">
                                    <h6 class="text-primary">üóëÔ∏è Right to Erasure</h6>
                                    <p class="small mb-0">Want to disappear from our system? We'll remove your data faster than evidence of that embarrassing impulse purchase (unless we have a legal reason to keep it).</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-6">
                            <div class="card bg-light border-0 h-100">
                                <div class="card-body">
                                    <h6 class="text-primary">üì¶ Right to Data Portability</h6>
                                    <p class="small mb-0">Want a copy of everything in a machine-readable format? We'll package it up nicely for you. Think of it as a digital scrapbook of your selling adventures.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="row mt-3">
                        <div class="col-md-6">
                            <div class="card bg-light border-0 h-100">
                                <div class="card-body">
                                    <h6 class="text-primary">‚è∏Ô∏è Right to Restrict Processing</h6>
                                    <p class="small mb-0">Want us to hold onto your data but not use it? We can put it in digital storage while we sort things out.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-6">
                            <div class="card bg-light border-0 h-100">
                                <div class="card-body">
                                    <h6 class="text-primary">üö´ Right to Object</h6>
                                    <p class="small mb-0">Don't like how we're processing your data? You can object, and we'll stop (unless we have compelling legitimate grounds to continue).</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="alert alert-info border-0 mt-4">
                        <h6><i class="fas fa-balance-scale me-2"></i>How to Exercise Your Rights</h6>
                        <p class="mb-2">To exercise any of these rights, just get in touch with us. Since this is a friends and family marketplace, you probably already know how to reach us! üòä</p>
                        <p class="small mb-2"><strong>Response Time:</strong> We'll respond within 1 month, as required by UK law. If your request is complex, we might need up to 3 months, but we'll let you know.</p>
                        <p class="small mb-0"><strong>Not Happy?</strong> If you're not satisfied with how we handle your request, you can complain to the <strong>Information Commissioner's Office (ICO)</strong> - they're the UK's data protection regulator. Visit <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" class="text-primary">ico.org.uk</a> or call 0303 123 1113.</p>
                    </div>

                    <h3 class="text-primary mb-3 mt-5">
                        <i class="fas fa-baby me-2"></i>Kids and Privacy
                    </h3>
                    <p>This site is designed for adults. If you're under 13, please ask your parents before using this site. If you're 13-17, make sure your parents are cool with you selling that Pokemon card collection.</p>

                    <h3 class="text-primary mb-3 mt-5">
                        <i class="fas fa-sync-alt me-2"></i>Changes to This Policy
                    </h3>
                    <p>Sometimes we might need to update this policy (hopefully to make it even funnier). When we do, we'll:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Post the new version here</li>
                        <li>Update the "last modified" date</li>
                        <li>Let you know if there are any major changes</li>
                        <li>Try to make the new version at least as entertaining as this one</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 class="text-primary mb-3 mt-5">
                        <i class="fas fa-question-circle me-2"></i>Questions? Concerns? Complaints About Our Ceramic Frog Jokes?
                    </h3>
                    <p>If you have any questions about this privacy policy, your data, or why we mentioned ceramic frogs so many times, feel free to reach out. Since this is a friends and family marketplace, you probably already have our contact info. üòâ</p>

                    <div class="alert alert-warning border-0 mt-4">
                        <h6><i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle me-2"></i>Important Legal Stuff</h6>
                        <p class="small mb-2">While we've tried to make this policy fun and readable, it's still a real legal document. We're serious about protecting your privacy, even if we're not serious about much else. This policy governs how we handle your personal information under UK data protection law.</p>
                        <p class="small mb-0"><strong>Legal Basis:</strong> We process your data based on legitimate interests (running our marketplace), contract performance (when you list items), and consent (for marketing, if any). We comply with UK GDPR and the Data Protection Act 2018.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="text-center mt-5 pt-4 border-top">
